article.headline: Colorado St. 83, North Florida 55
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Greg Smith had 15 points, seven rebounds and five assists and Colorado State pulled away in the second half to beat North Florida 83-55 Monday night. Pierce Hornung had 13 points and seven rebounds while Dorian Green contributed 13 points and five assists for the Rams (7-2), who bounced back from losses to Colorado and Illinois-Chicago. Colton Iverson had 10 points and Daniel Bejarano shared rebounding honors with seven. Colorado State was 7 for 11 from 3-point range and extended its seven-point halftime lead to as many as the final margin of 28. Travis Wallace led the Ospreys (3-7) with 12 points. Parker Smith added 10 points. The Rams owned a 41-23 rebounding edge and held North Florida to 43 percent shooting -- 36 percent in the second half.
